description:
&lt;p&gt;Manchester Foundation Trust is looking to recruit a dynamic and enthusiastic registered nurse to join the multidisciplinary team within The Manchester Pain Service. The postholder will be expected to work across the acute- chronic spectrum of pain giving support and advice to patients in both the inpatient and outpatient environment. While we have an integrated pain service across all hospital sites, the post holder with be primarily based at Wythenshawe hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will possess good communication skills, able to demonstrate an aptitude for working independently, as well as in a team, and have good management and clinical skills. They will participate in the development, delivery and evaluation of the Pain Service. The post holder will need to be flexible, self-motivated and committed to the challenges of maintaining our high quality standards of care for all our patients within this ever growing speciality. It is essential that any applicants have at least 2 years post registration experience in a speciality related to acute or chronic pain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your on-going professional development will be actively encouraged and supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJillian ProbertJob titleMatronEmail addressjillian.probert@mft.nhs.ukTelephone number07816348958&lt;/p&gt;
